                <note rend="inline" type="source">452.11/198: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blake</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-07T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Department mail instruction 438, October 18. Please expedite.</p>
                <p>The Department has suggested to the Spanish Embassy here that the claims be
                    examined by a Commission consisting of you and the Spanish Consul General at
                    Tangier and that you draw up a joint report of findings and recommendations to
                    be submitted to the two Governments. Upon receipt of a reply from the Spanish
                    Embassy telegraphic instructions will be addressed to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
